Issue #1: Service Won't Start
  Solution:
    1. Check logs: docker-compose logs service-name
    2. Restart service: docker-compose restart service-name
    3. Full rebuild: docker-compose down && docker-compose up -d

Issue #2: Health Check Failures
  Solution:
    1. Test health endpoint: curl http://localhost:PORT/health
    2. Check service logs: docker-compose logs service-name
    3. Verify dependencies: docker-compose exec service-name ping dependency-service

Issue #3: Port Conflicts
  Solution:
    1. Find process: lsof -i :PORT
    2. Update docker-compose.yml port mappings
    3. Restart services: docker-compose restart

Issue #4: Memory/CPU Issues
  Solution:
    1. Check resource usage: docker stats
    2. Adjust limits in docker-compose.yml
    3. Restart services: docker-compose up -d

Issue #5: Database Connection Errors
  Solution:
    1. Test MongoDB: docker-compose exec backend curl http://mongo:27017
    2. Check connection string: docker-compose exec backend env | grep DATABASE
    3. Reset database: docker-compose down -v && docker-compose up -d

Debug Commands:
  Enter container: docker-compose exec backend bash
  Check env vars: docker-compose exec backend env | grep FL_
  Test connectivity: docker-compose exec backend ping mongo
  Check mounted volumes: docker-compose exec backend ls -la /models
  View resource limits: docker inspect sovereignmap-fl | grep -A 20 Resources
